            <scopecontent>
               <head>Scope and Contents</head>
                                 <p>The correspondence in this collection is between various members of the Hastings and Willson families of Ohio. Letters from the Civil War period comment on the draft and Morgan&#039;s Raid, while later letters discuss weather, crops, and family matters.</p>
                                 <p>Leland Baird, a descendant of the Hastings and Willson families, loaned the collection to the Library for photocopying in 1973.</p>
                        </scopecontent>
            


